Pair with **session-start** rule: `bash scripts/init-project-rules.sh --project <workspace>`

# Session end — memory checklist

When the user ends a session, mentions distill, or you see `[agent-memory] Session end` in context:

## 1. Read hook log (if exists)

```text
~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory-session.log
```

Last lines contain the sessionEnd checklist (also in stderr during hook run).

## 2. Execute checklist

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| Forward pointer | Hooks write regex **## Next step** — if `[?]` / `_No forward pointer._` / low-confidence hook msg → `pointer-curate-prompt.md` |
| Distill | Review `merge-staging/`; curate **## Decisions** from staging |
| Fallback | If distill lacks detail → open chat link `[title](uuid)` in ## Recent |
| Verify | `verify-memory.py --memory-home $MEMORY_HOME` |
| Pending | `list-chats.py --pending` — note unprocessed chats |

## 3. Semantic merge (not optional for new distill)

- `--apply` updates **Recent** + **Next step** — never replaces agent curation of `## Decisions`
- Use skill **semantic-merge** + `templates/chats/semantic-merge-prompt.md`
- Pointer only: `templates/chats/pointer-curate-prompt.md`

## Paths

- Framework: `$FRAMEWORK_ROOT` from `~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory.env`
- Hub: `$MEMORY_HOME` from hook env or `<install>/memory/config.json`
- Edit log: `~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory-edit.log`

Install hooks: `bash scripts/install-memory-hooks.sh`
